    <note>Chen(1) Yizhong [15991] He entered the imperial university and, along with Huang(2) Yong(3) [15994] (q.v.) and four other students, sent up a memorial attacking Ding(1) Daquan [15990], who became angry and had him expelled and exiled. When he was chief minister of state a second time under the Yiwang (?), he planned to take him into exile in Champa. He left and fled to Champa first and did not return. CHECK details. Zhejiang TZm 128.30a. CBD, 3, 2586-7.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1273:  Apt. Tong qianshu Shumi yuan shi (State Council).1274:  Promoted to Qianshu Shumi yuan shi and apt. concurrently Canzhi zhengshi (Duzong dead/Jia Sidao out)1275:  Apt. Zuo chengxiang.1275:  Dismissed to a temple sinecure.1276:  After reappointment as Zuo chengxiang, he fled to Champa.</note>
